msgstr "afaylu / akaram ur izmir ara ad yeldi"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:667
msgid "Dialogs:"
msgstr "Idiwenniyen:"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:711
msgid "Search in path when query contains path separators"
msgstr "Nadi deg ubrid mi ara yili deg tuttra imnabḍen n ubrid"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:750
msgid "Hide results when search is empty"
msgstr "Ffer igmaḍ mi ara tili unadi d ilem"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:769
msgid "Match case when query contains at least one upper case character"
msgstr ""
"Qadaṛ amasal n isekkilen mi ara yili deg tuttra ma drus yiwen usekkil "
"ameqqran"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:855
msgid ""
"<b>Enable dark theme:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the system theme is asked to use a darker styling for the "
"application <i>(i.e. dark UI elements on bright text)</i>.\n"
"\n"
"Note that not all system themes provide such a darker variant, therefore "
"enabling this setting might not have an effect."
msgstr ""
"<b>Rmed asentel aberkan:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, asentel n unagraw ad yettusutreḍ ad iseqdec aɣanib uḍlim i usnas "
"<i>(d aselmed, iferdisen iberkanen n ugrudem ɣef uḍris aceɛlal)</i>.\n"
"\n"
"Ẓer belli mačči akk isental n unagraw i d-yettakken lqem-a uḍlim, ihi armad "
"n yiɣewwar-a yezmer ur d-yeglu s kra n ubeddel."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:873
msgid ""
"<b>Enable client-side decorations:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the search entry and main menu are displayed in the window title "
"bar.\n"
"\n"
"If disabled, the main menu is displayed as a menu bar with the search entry "
"below it.\n"
"This resembles a more traditional UI layout and takes a little bit more "
"space."
msgstr ""
"<b>Rmed adlag n tama n umsaɣ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, anekcum n unadi akked wumuɣ agejdan ad d-banen deg ufeggag n "
"uzwel n usfaylu.\n"
"\n"
"Ma yensa, umuɣ agejdan ad d-iban d afeggag n wumuɣ, anekcum n unadi daw-as.\n"
"Ayagi icuba ugar taneɣruft n ugrudem tansayt, yerna yettaṭṭaf cwiṭ ugar n "
"umḍiq."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:893
msgid ""
"<b>Use binary units instead of decimal units:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This settings controls how file sizes are displayed.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>Binary units:</b> This refers to binary IEC prefixes <i>(e.g. 1 KiB = "
"1024 bytes)</i>\n"
"\t• <b>Decimal  units:</b> This refers to decimal SI prefixes <i>(e.g. 1 kB "
"= 1000 bytes)</i>"
msgstr ""
"<b>Seqdec iferdisen imisin deg umḍiq n iferdisen imrawanen:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Iɣewwaren-a ttseyyiḍen amek ara d-banent tiddiwin n ifuyla.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>Iferdisen imisin:</b> Ayagi yettuɣal ɣer izwiren imisin n IEC "
"<i>(amedya 1 KiB = 1024 bytes)</i>\n"
"\t• <b>Iferdisen imrawanen:</b> Ayagi yettuɣal ɣer izwiren imrawanen n SI "
"<i>(amedya 1 kB = 1000 bytes)</i>"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:913
msgid ""
"<b>Remember window size:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the window size from the previous session will be restored when "
"you open an FSearch window.\n"
"\n"
"Note that some window managers ignore this request and force the window to "
"have a different size."
msgstr ""
"<b>Mekti tiddi n usfaylu:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, tiddi n usfaylu n tɣimit yezrin ad d-tuɣal mi ara teldiḍ asfaylu "
"n FSearch.\n"
"\n"
"Ẓer belli kra n imsefraken n isfuyla ttanfen asuter-a, yerna ttḥettimen ɣef "
"usfaylu ad yesɛu tiddi-nniḍen."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:932
msgid ""
"<b>Behaviour after successfully opening a file:</b>\n"
"\n"
"When a file/folder was successfully opened one of the following actions can "
"be performed:\n"
"\t• <b>Nothing:</b> Nothing happens.\n"
"                        • <b>Minimize:</b> The currently selected FSearch "
"window becomes minimized.\n"
"\t• <b>Close:</b> Quit FSearch.\n"
"\n"
"You can configure if those actions should be triggered when the file was "
"opened with\n"
"\t• <b>keyboard shortcuts or menu entries</b> and/or\n"
"\t• <b>mouse click</b>"
msgstr ""
"<b>Tiddin mbaɛd ma yeldi ufaylu akken iwata:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Mi ara yeldi ufaylu/ukaram akken iwata, yiwen seg tigawin-a yezmer ad "
"yettwag:\n"
"\t• <b>Ulac:</b> Ur d-ḍerru kra.\n"
"                        • <b>Semẓi:</b> Asfaylu n FSearch yettwafernen akka "
"tura ad yettusemẓi.\n"
"\t• <b>Mdel:</b> Ffeɣ seg FSearch.\n"
"\n"
"Tzemreḍ ad tsewleḍ ma yella tigawin-a ad ttwaremdent mi ara yeldi ufaylu s\n"
"\t• <b>inegzumen n unasiw neɣ inekcumen n wumuɣ</b> akked/neɣ\n"
"\t• <b>usiti n umumed</b>"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:956
msgid ""
"<b>Show highlighted search terms:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the search terms will be highlighted in the results view. For "
"example when you search for \"foo\" all appearances of <i>foo</i> in file/"
"folder names will be highlighted with bold characters:\n"
"\n"
"\t<b>foo</b>bar.txt\n"
"\tfile.<b>foo</b>\n"
"\n"
"This also works for regular expressions and wildcard expressions starting or "
"ending with an asterisk. "
msgstr ""
"<b>Sken awalen n unadi yettusebruren:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, awalen n unadi ad ttusebruren deg tmuɣli n igmaḍ. D amedya, mi "
"ara tnadiḍ \"foo\", akk timlilitin n <i>foo</i> deg yismawen n ifuyla/"
"ikaramen ad ttusebrurent s isekkilen izuranen:\n"
"\n"
"\t<b>foo</b>bar.txt\n"
"\tfile.<b>foo</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ayagi iteddu daɣen i tinfaliyin tiluganin akked tinfaliyin tilelliyin "
"ibeddun neɣ ifakkan s teṛṣemt. "

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:978
msgid ""
"<b>Show tooltips:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the results view will show the full path of the focused file/"
"folder in a small tooltip window."
msgstr ""
"<b>Sken tilɣa n yifecka:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, taskant n igmaḍ ad tesken abrid ummid n ufaylu/ukaram "
"yettwafernen deg usfaylu ameẓyan n telɣut n yifecka."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:995
msgid ""
"<b>Show icons in name column:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, file/folder icons will be shown in the name column."
msgstr ""
"<b>Sken tidwirin deg tgejdit n yisem:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, tidwirin n ufaylu/ukaram ad ttuseknent deg tgejdit n yisem."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1012
msgid ""
"<b>Remember column configuration:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the column configuration of the results view from the previous "
"session will be restored when you open an FSearch window. This includes the "
"size and visibility of all columns."
msgstr ""
"<b>Mmekti tawila n tgejdit:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, tawila n tgejdit n tmuɣli n igmaḍ seg tɣimit yezrin ad d-tuɣal mi "
"ara teldiḍ asfaylu n FSearch. Ayagi iteddu ula ɣer teɣzi d tbanit n merra "
"tigejda."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1029
msgid ""
"<b>Remember sort order:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the sort order of the results view from the previous session "
"will be restored when you open an FSearch window."
msgstr ""
"<b>Mmekti amizzwer n usmizzwer:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, amizzwer n usmizzwer n tmuɣli n igmaḍ seg tɣimit yezrin ad d-"
"yuɣal mi ara teldiḍ asfaylu n FSearch."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1046
msgid ""
"<b>Open path with double click in path column:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, double clicking in the path column will open the selected path."
msgstr ""
"<b>Ldi abrid s usiti uslig deg tgejdit n ubrid:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, asiti uslig deg tgejdit n ubrid ad yeldi abrid yettwafernen."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1063
msgid ""
"<b>Single click to open:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, a single click will open the selected file/folder. If you only "
"want to select a file/folder while this setting is active, you need to hold "
"<i>Ctrl</i> at the same time while clicking the file/folder."
msgstr ""
"<b>Yan usiti i welday:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, yan usiti ad yeldi afaylu/akaram yettwafernen. Ma tebɣiḍ kan ad "
"tferneḍ afaylu/akaram mi ara yili usgaddi-a yermed, issefk ad teṭṭfeḍ "
"<i>Ctrl</i> deg yimir-nni mi ara tessitiḍ ɣef ufaylu/ukaram."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1080
msgid ""
"<b>Show database indexing status:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the path that is currently being indexed is displayed in the "
"statusbar."
msgstr ""
"<b>Sken addad n usmiter n taffa n isefka:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, abrid i yettusmitiren akka tura ad d-yettwaskan deg ufeggag n "
"waddad."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1097
msgid ""
"<b>Show warning dialogs:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, a warning dialog is displayed when a file or folder failed to "
"open."
msgstr ""
"<b>Sken idiwenniyen n ulɣu:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, ad d-yettwaskan udiwenni n ulɣu mi ara yili ufaylu neɣ akaram ur "
"izmir ara ad yeldi."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1114
msgid ""
"<b>Search in path when query contains path separators:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, search terms containing path separators (i.e. \"/\") will be "
"automatically matched against the full path of a file or folder."
msgstr ""
"<b>Nadi deg ubrid mi ara tesɛu tuttra imnabḍen n ubrid:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, irmawen n unadi i yesɛan imnabḍen n ubrid (am \"/\") ad "
"ttwacudden s wudem awurman ɣer ubrid ummid n ufaylu neɣ ukaram."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1131
msgid ""
"<b>Match case when query contains at least one upper case character:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, search terms containing at least one upper case character will "
"trigger a case-sensitive search. This means a search term like <i>Foo</i> "
"will match <i>FooBar.txt</i> but not <i>foobar.txt</i>."
msgstr ""
"<b>Qader talɣa n isekkilen mi ara tesɛu tuttra ma drus yiwen usekkil "
"ameqqran:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, irmawen n unadi i yesɛan ma drus yiwen usekkil ameqqran ad sekren "
"anadi yettḥulfun i talɣa n isekkilen. Ayagi yebɣa ad yini d akken awal n "
"unadi am <i>Foo</i> ad yemṣada d <i>FooBar.txt</i> maca ur yemṣada ara d "
"<i>foobar.txt</i>."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1148
msgid ""
"<b>Hide results when search is empty:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, no search results are displayed when the search entry is empty.\n"
"\n"
"If disabled, all files and folders will be displayed when the search entry "
"is empty."
msgstr ""
"<b>Ffer igmaḍ mi ara yili unadi d ilem:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, ulac igmaḍ n unadi ara d-yettwasknen mi ara yili unekcum n unadi "
"d ilem.\n"
"\n"
"Ma yensa, merra ifuyla d ikaramen ad d-ttwasknen mi ara yili unekcum n unadi "
"d ilem."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1167
msgid ""
"<b>Search as you type:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the search is automatically updated with every keystroke.\n"
"\n"
"If disabled, the search is only updated when you hit <i>Enter</i> or press "
"the search button. "
msgstr ""
"<b>ⴰⵔⵣⵣⵓ ⵍⵍⵉⵖ ⴰⵔ ⵜⴰⵔⴰⴷ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⴰⴷ ⵉⵎⵓⵛⵛⵓ ⵓⵔⵣⵣⵓ ⵙ ⵓⵡⵓⵔⵎ ⵙ ⴽⵓ ⵜⵉⴽⴽⵉ ⵅⴼ ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⵙⴰⵔⵓ.\n"
"\n"
"ⵎⴽ ⵉⵏⵙ, ⵓⵔ ⵉⵜⵜⵎⵓⵛⵛⵓ ⵓⵔⵣⵣⵓ ⴰⵔ ⵙⴽⵓⴷ ⵜⴽⴽⵉⴷ ⵅⴼ <i>Enter</i> ⵏⵉⵖ ⵜⵙⴷⴷⵉⴷ ⵜⴰⵇⴼⴰⵍⵜ ⵏ "
"ⵓⵔⵣⵣⵓ. "

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1186
msgid ""
"<b>Update database on start:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, the database will be updated automatically in the background "
"when you start FSearch."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⵎⵓⵛⵛⵓ ⵜⴰⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ ⴳ ⵜⵏⴽⵔⴰ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⴰⴷ ⵜⵎⵓⵛⵛⵓ ⵜⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ ⵙ ⵓⵡⵓⵔⵎ ⴳ ⵓⴷⵉⵔ ⵍⵍⵉⵖ ⵜⵙⵙⵏⴽⴰⵔⴷ FSearch."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1203
msgid ""
"<b>Included folders:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This list contains all folders you want to include in the database.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>Active:</b> If enabled, the path will included in the database to be "
"searched in.\n"
"\t• <b>Path:</b> The full path to be included.\n"
"\t• <b>One Filesystem:</b> If enabled, FSearch won't cross filesystem "
"boundaries for this folder"
msgstr ""
"<b>ⵉⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎⵏ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵎⴷⵏ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵜⴰⴱⴷⴰⵔⵜ ⴰⴷ ⵍⵍⴰⵏ ⴳⵉⵙ ⴰⴽⴽⵯ ⵉⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎⵏ ⵍⵍⵉ ⵜⵔⵉⴷ ⴰⴷ ⵜⵏ ⵜⵙⵎⴷⴷ ⴳ ⵜⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>ⵉⵔⵎⴷ:</b> ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⴰⴷ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵎⴷ ⵓⴱⵔⵉⴷ ⴳ ⵜⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ ⴰⴼ ⴰⴷ ⴳⵉⵙ ⵉⵍⵉ "
"ⵓⵔⵣⵣⵓ.\n"
"\t• <b>ⴰⴱⵔⵉⴷ:</b> ⴰⴱⵔⵉⴷ ⵓⵎⵎⵉⴷ ⵍⵍⵉ ⵔⴰⴷ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵎⴷ.\n"
"\t• <b>ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ:</b> ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⵓⵔ ⵉⵔⴰⴷ FSearch ⴰⴷ ⵉⵣⵔⵉ ⵜⵉⵍⵉⵙⴰ ⵏ "
"ⵓⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ ⵉ ⵓⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⴰⴷ"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1224
msgid ""
"<b>Add folder to database:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This button opens a dialog where you can select a folder you want to include "
"in the database for searching."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⵔⵏⵓ ⴰⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⵖⵔ ⵜⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵜⴰⵇⴼⴰⵍⵜ ⴰⴷ ⴰⵔ ⵜⵙⵙⵔⴳⵎ ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⴷⵉⵡⵏⵏⵉ ⵎⴰⵏⵉ ⵜⵣⵎⵔⴷ ⴰⴷ ⵜⵙⵜⵢⴷ ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⵍⵍⵉ ⵜⵔⵉⴷ ⴰⴷ "
"ⵜ ⵜⵙⵎⴷⴷ ⴳ ⵜⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ ⵉ ⵓⵔⵣⵣⵓ."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1241
msgid ""
"<b>Add a specific path:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Type the full path of a folder here and click the button next to it to "
"include that folder in the database. This is useful for adding a path "
"directly without browsing for it."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⵔⵏⵓ ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⴱⵔⵉⴷ ⵓⵙⴷⵉⴷ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⴰⵔⴰ ⴷⴰ ⴰⴱⵔⵉⴷ ⵓⵎⵎⵉⴷ ⵏ ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ, ⵜⵙⴷⴷⵉⴷ ⵜⴰⵇⴼⴰⵍⵜ ⵍⵍⵉ ⴷⴰⵔⵙ ⵜⵣⴷⵉⴳ ⴰⴼ ⴰⴷ ⵜⵙⵎⴷⴷ "
"ⴰⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⴰⴷ ⴳ ⵜⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ. ⴰⵢⴰ ⵉⵏⴼⵄ ⵉ ⵓⵔⵏⴰⵡ ⵏ ⵓⴱⵔⵉⴷ ⵙ ⵓⵙⵔⵉⴷ, ⴱⵍⴰ ⴰⵙⵙⵉⵔⴰ "
"ⵏⵏⵙ."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1258
msgid ""
"<b>Remove selected row:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This removes the selected folder from the list of included folders."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⴽⴽⵙ ⴰⴷⵓⵔ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵜⵢⵏ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⴰⵢⴰ ⴰⵔ ⵉⵜⵜⴽⴽⵙ ⴰⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵜⵢⵏ ⵙⴳ ⵜⴱⴷⴰⵔⵜ ⵏ ⵉⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎⵏ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵎⴷⵏ."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1275
msgid ""
"<b>Attempt to monitor:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, FSearch watches this folder for changes and keeps the database "
"up to date automatically, so you don't have to rescan manually.\n"
"\n"
"Monitoring isn't supported on every file system and uses a small amount of "
"system resources per watched folder. For large directory trees with many "
"files the system may run out of resources to watch them all."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⴰⵄⵔⴰⴹ ⵏ ⵓⵙⵙⵓⴷⵎ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⴰⴷ ⵉⵙⵙⵓⴷⵎ FSearch ⴰⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⴰⴷ ⵉ ⵉⵙⵏⴼⴰⵍ, ⵉⵙⵙⵎⵓⵛⵛⵓ ⵜⴰⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ ⵙ "
"ⵓⵡⵓⵔⵎ, ⴰⴼ ⴰⴷ ⵓⵔ ⵜⵙⵔⵉⴷ ⴰⵍⵍⵓⵎⵎⵓⵥ ⵙ ⵓⴼⵓⵙ.\n"
"\n"
"ⵓⵔ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵙⵏⴷ ⵓⵙⵙⵓⴷⵎ ⴳ ⴽⵓ ⴰⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ, ⴰⵔ ⵉⵙⵙⵎⵔⴰⵙ ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⴳⵣⵣⵓⵎ ⴰⵎⵥⵥⵢⴰⵏ ⵙⴳ "
"ⵜⵖⴱⵓⵍⴰ ⵏ ⵓⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡ ⵉ ⴽⵓ ⴰⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵙⵓⴷⵎⵏ. ⵉ ⵉⵙⴽⵍⴰ ⵉⵎⵇⵇⵔⴰⵏⵏ ⵏ ⵉⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎⵏ ⵉⵍⵍⴰⵏ "
"ⴷⴰⵔⵙⵏ ⴰⵟⵟⴰⵚ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ, ⵉⵣⵎⵔ ⴰⴷ ⴼⴰⵡⵏⵜ ⵜⵖⴱⵓⵍⴰ ⵏ ⵓⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡ ⴰⴼ ⴰⴷ ⵜⵏ ⵉⵙⵙⵓⴷⵎ ⴰⴽⴽⵯ."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1294
msgid ""
"<b>Scan after launch:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, this folder is rescanned every time FSearch starts, so the "
"database reflects any changes made while FSearch wasn't running."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⴰⵍⵍⵓⵎⵎⵓⵥ ⴹⴰⵕⵜ ⵏ ⵓⵙⵙⵏⴽⵔ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⴰⴷ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵍⵓⵎⵎⵓⵥ ⵓⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⴰⴷ ⵙ ⵓⵡⴷⵎ ⴰⵎⴰⵢⵏⵓ ⴽⵓ ⵜⵉⴽⴽⵍⵜ ⵍⵍⵉⵖ ⵉⵜⵜⵏⴽⴰⵔ "
"FSearch, ⴰⴼ ⴰⴷ ⵜⵙⴽⵏ ⵜⴷⴰⵙⵉⵍⵜ ⵏ ⵉⵙⴼⴽⴰ ⴽⵓ ⵉⵙⵏⴼⴰⵍ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⴳⴰⵏ ⵍⵍⵉⵖ ⵓⵔ ⵉⵜⵜⵎⴰⵙⴰ "
"FSearch."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1311
msgid ""
"<b>Stay on one file system:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, FSearch won't cross file system boundaries while scanning this "
"folder. Mounted file systems below it (e.g. external drives or network "
"shares) are skipped."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⵇⵇⵉⵎ ⴳ ⵢⴰⵏ ⵓⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⵓⵔ ⵉⵔⴰⴷ FSearch ⴰⴷ ⵉⵣⵔⵉ ⵜⵉⵍⵉⵙⴰ ⵏ ⵓⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ ⵍⵍⵉⵖ ⴰⵔ ⵉⵍⵓⵎⵎⵓⵥ "
"ⴰⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⴰⴷ. ⴰⴷ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵣⵔⵉ ⵉⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡⵏ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵙⵔⵙⵏ ⴷⴷⴰⵡ ⴰⵙ (ⴰⵎ ⵉⵎⵙⵙⵓⴷⵙⵏ "
"ⵉⴱⵕⵕⴰⵏⵉⵢⵏ ⵏⵉⵖ ⵉⴱⴹⴰⵏ ⵏ ⵓⵥⵟⵟⴰ)."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1328
msgid ""
"<b>Rescan every:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, this folder is rescanned automatically at the given interval. "
"Use the hours and minutes fields to set how often the rescan happens.\n"
"\n"
"This is useful for folders on file systems that can't be monitored for "
"changes."
msgstr ""
"<b>ⴰⵍⵍⵓⵎⵎⵓⵥ ⵙ ⵓⵡⴰⵍ ⴽⵓ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"ⵎⴽ ⵉⵔⵎⴷ, ⴰⴷ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⵍⵓⵎⵎⵓⵥ ⵓⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎ ⴰⴷ ⵙ ⵓⵡⵓⵔⵎ ⴳ ⵓⵣⵎⵣ ⵉⵜⵜⵓⴼⴽⴰⵏ. ⵙⵙⵎⵔⵙ ⵉⴳⵔⴰⵏ ⵏ "
"ⵜⵙⵔⴰⴳⵉⵏ ⴷ ⵜⵓⵙⴷⵉⴷⵉⵏ ⴰⴼ ⴰⴷ ⵜⵙⴱⴷⴷⴷ ⵎⵏⵛⴽ ⵏ ⵜⵉⴽⴽⴰⵍ ⵍⵍⵉ ⴳ ⵉⵜⵜⵉⵍⵉ ⵓⵍⵍⵓⵎⵎⵓⵥ.\n"
"\n"
"ⴰⵢⴰ ⵉⵏⴼⵄ ⵉ ⵉⴽⴰⵔⴰⵎⵏ ⵉⵍⵍⴰⵏ ⴳ ⵉⵏⴳⵔⴰⵡⵏ ⵏ ⵉⴼⵓⵢⵍⴰ ⵍⵍⵉ ⵓⵔ ⵉⵣⵎⵉⵔ ⵓⵙⵙⵓⴷⵎ ⵏ ⵉⵙⵏⴼⴰⵍ "
"ⵏⵏⵙⵏ."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1347
msgid ""
"<b>Exclude rules:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This list contains rules for the files and folders you want to exclude from "
"the database.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>Active:</b> If enabled, the rule is applied and matching items are "
"excluded.\n"
"\t• <b>Pattern:</b> The text matched against each item, interpreted "
"according to the Type.\n"
"\t• <b>Type:</b> How the pattern is interpreted — <i>Literal</i> (exact "
"text), <i>Wildcard</i> (using * and ?) or <i>Regex</i> (a regular "
"expression).\n"
"\t• <b>Match:</b> Whether the pattern is matched against the item's <i>Full "
"Path</i> or only its <i>Basename</i> (the name without the path).\n"
"\t• <b>Applies To:</b> Whether the rule affects <i>Files</i>, <i>Folders</i> "
"or both."
msgstr ""
"<b>Ilugan n usuffeɣ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Tabdart-a tesɛa ilugan i ifuyla d ikaramen i tebɣiḍ ad tsuffɣeḍ seg taffa n "
"isefka.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>Urmid:</b> Ma yermed, ad yettwasnes ulug, ad ttwassuffɣen yiferdisen "
"imeɣran.\n"
"\t• <b>Udlif:</b> Aḍris i yettameɣran ɣef yal aferdis, yettwafham ilmend n "
"Wanaw.\n"
"\t• <b>Anaw:</b> Amek yettwafham udlif — <i>Aḍris usrid</i> (aḍris ameɣtu), "
"<i>Azamul amaway</i> (s useqdec n * d ?) neɣ <i>Regex</i> (tanfalit "
"talugant).\n"
"\t• <b>Amṣada:</b> Ma yella udlif ad yettameɣri ɣef <i>Ubrid ummid</i> n "
"uferdis neɣ ɣef <i>Yisem n ufaylu</i> kan (isem war abrid).\n"
"\t• <b>Yettwasnes ɣef:</b> Ma yella ulug ad iḥaz <i>Ifuyla</i>, <i>Ikaramen</"
"i> neɣ i sin."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1370
msgid ""
"<b>Add exclude rule:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This adds a new, empty rule to the list. Edit its Pattern, Type, Match and "
"Applies To columns to control what gets excluded from the database."
msgstr ""
"<b>Rnu alugen n usuffeɣ:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ayagi ad yernu ar tebdart alugen amaynut ilem. Ẓreg tigejda-ines Udlif, "
"Anaw, Amṣada d Yettwasnes ɣef iwakken ad tsenqdeḍ acu ara yettwassuffɣen seg "
"taffa n isefka."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1387
msgid ""
"<b>Remove selected row:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This removes the selected rule from the list of exclude rules."
msgstr ""
"<b>Kkes izirig yettwafernen:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ayagi ad yekkes alugen yettwafernen seg tebdart n ilugan n usuffeɣ."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1404
msgid ""
"<b>Restore default exclude rules:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This button restores the default set of exclude rules.\n"
"\n"
"⚠ All rules which were created or edited by the user will be lost! ⚠"
msgstr ""
"<b>Err-d ilugan n usuffeɣ n lexṣas:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Taqeffalt-a ad d-terr tagrumma n lexṣas n ilugan n usuffeɣ.\n"
"\n"
"⚠ Akk ilugan i d-yerna neɣ i yeẓreg useqdac ad ṛuḥen! ⚠"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1423
msgid ""
"<b>Exclude files and folders from database:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This is a semi-colon separated list of files (or folders) you want to "
"exclude from the database. For example <i>.git;.cache;*.swp</i> will exclude "
"all files or folders which are called either <i>.git</i> or <i>.cache</i> or "
"end with <i>.swp</i>."
msgstr ""
"<b>Suffeɣ ifuyla d ikaramen seg taffa n isefka:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Tagi d tabdart n ifuyla (neɣ ikaramen) i tebɣiḍ ad tsuffɣeḍ seg taffa n "
"isefka, ttwabḍan s wagaz n ticcert. Amedya, <i>.git;.cache;*.swp</i> ad "
"isuffeɣ akk ifuyla neɣ ikaramen i wumi qqaren <i>.git</i> neɣ <i>.cache</i>, "
"neɣ i ikeffun s <i>.swp</i>."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1440
msgid ""
"<b>Exclude hidden files and folders:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, hidden files and folders will be excluded from the database "
"<i>(i.e. all files or folders which start with a dot character)</i>."
msgstr ""
"<b>Suffeɣ ifuyla d ikaramen uffiren:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, ifuyla d ikaramen uffiren ad ttwassuffɣen seg taffa n isefka "
"<i>(anamek-is, akk ifuyla neɣ ikaramen i ibeddun s uzamul n wagaz)</i>."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1457
msgid "Focus a setting to get a detailed description of what it does."
msgstr ""
"Err asaḍas ɣef yiwen n useɣwer iwakken ad tawiḍ aglam leqqayen n wayen "
"ixeddem."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1470
msgid ""
"<b>Periodically update database at a specific time interval:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled and as long as FSearch is running, the database will be updated "
"periodically with the given time interval.\n"
"\n"
"If you want to update the database in the background, even when FSearch is "
"not running, you should use tools like cron or systemd timers to "
"periodically trigger the update with:\n"
"\n"
"<i><tt>fsearch --update-database</tt></i>"
msgstr ""
"<b>Leqqem taffa n isefka s wudem uslig deg tallunt n wakud yettwafernen:</"
"b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, skud FSearch iteddu, taffa n isefka ad tettwaleqqem s wudem uslig "
"s tallunt n wakud i d-yettunefken.\n"
"\n"
"Ma tebɣiḍ ad tleqqmeḍ taffa n isefka deg ugilal, ula ma FSearch ur iteddu "
"ara, issefk ad tesqedceḍ ifecka am cron neɣ imeswaq n systemd iwakken ad "
"teskerḍeḍ aleqqem s wudem uslig s:\n"
"\n"
"<i><tt>fsearch --update-database</tt></i>"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1491
msgid ""
"<b>Launch desktop files:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, activating a <i>.desktop</i> file will launch the application "
"defined within that file. This way FSearch can act like an application "
"launcher. Otherwise the <i>.desktop</i> file will be opened with the default "
"handler for this type of files, which is usually a text editor."
msgstr ""
"<b>Sekker ifuyla n tnarit:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, asermed n ufaylu <i>.desktop</i> ad isekker asnas yettusbadun deg "
"ufaylu-nni. S wakka FSearch yezmer ad yeddu am usekkar n isnasen. Ma ulac, "
"afaylu <i>.desktop</i> ad yeldi s umsefrak n lexṣas n wanaw-a n ifuyla, i "
"yettilin s umata d amaẓrag n uḍris."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1508
msgid ""
"<b>Filters:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This is a list of all available filters. A filter is a predefined search.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>Name:</b> A unique and descriptive identifier for the filter\n"
"\t• <b>Macro:</b> By typing the macro text followed by a ':' you can enable "
"the filter on demand\n"
"\t• <b>Query:</b> The search term by which the database should be filtered"
msgstr ""
"<b>Imzizdigen:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Tagi d tabdart n yimzizdigen akk yellan. Imzizdeg d unadi yettusbadun s "
"uzwir.\n"
"\n"
"\t• <b>Isem:</b> Asulay asuf d unaglam n umzizdeg\n"
"\t• <b>Amakru:</b> S tira n uḍris n umakru, yeḍfer-it ':' tzemreḍ ad "
"tesremdeḍ amizizdeg ɣef usuter\n"
"\t• <b>Tuttra:</b> Awal n unadi s wayes ara yettwazizdeg taffa n isefka"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1529
msgid ""
"<b>Add a new filter:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This button opens a dialog where you can edit a new filter."
msgstr ""
"<b>Rnu imsizdeg amaynu:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Taqeffalt ad teldi adiwenni anida i tzemreḍ ad tẓergeḍ imsizdeg amaynu."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1546
msgid ""
"<b>Remove selected filter:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This button removes the currently selected filter."
msgstr ""
"<b>Kkes imsizdeg yettwafernen:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Taqeffalt ad tekkes imsizdeg yettwafernen tura."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1563
msgid ""
"<b>Edit selected filter:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This button opens a dialog where you can edit the selected filter."
msgstr ""
"<b>Ẓreg imsizdeg yettwafernen:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Taqeffalt ad teldi adiwenni anida i tzemreḍ ad tẓergeḍ imsizdeg yettwafernen."

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1580
msgid ""
"<b>Restore default filters:</b>\n"
"\n"
"This button restores the default filter configuration.\n"
"\n"
"⚠ All filters which were created or edited by the user will be lost! ⚠"
msgstr ""
"<b>Err-d imsizdigen imezwar:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Taqeffalt ad terr-d tawila tamezwarut n imsizdigen.\n"
"\n"
"⚠ Akk imsizdigen i d-yerna neɣ i yeẓreg useqdac ad ṛuḥen! ⚠"

#: src/fsearch_preferences.ui:1599
msgid ""
"<b>Exit on Escape:</b>\n"
"\n"
"If enabled, FSearch exits when the Escape key is pressed instead of the "
"window being minimized."
msgstr ""
"<b>Ffeɣ s Escape:</b>\n"
"\n"
"Ma yermed, FSearch ad yeffeɣ mi ara tettwasḍas tqeffalt Escape, deg umḍiq n "
"usemẓi n usfaylu."

#: src/fsearch_result_view.c:381
msgid "Invalid row data"
msgstr "Isefka n wadur mačči d imeɣta"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.c:80
msgid "Querying…"
msgstr "Anadi…"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:52
msgid "Number of Search Results"
msgstr "Amḍan n igmaḍ n unadi"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:153
msgid "Index:"
msgstr "Amatar:"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:369
msgid "Number of database items"
msgstr "Amḍan n iferdisen n taffa n isefka"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:407
msgid ""
"Search term contains upper case characters.\n"
"<b>Match Case</b> was temporarily activated for this term."
msgstr ""
"Awal n unadi igber isekkilen imeqqranen.\n"
"<b>Amṣada n usekkil</b> irmed i kra n wakud i wawal-a."

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:438 src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:491
msgid "CASE"
msgstr "ASEKKIL"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:514
msgid ""
"Search term contains path separators.\n"
"<b>Search in Path</b> was temporarily activated for this term."
msgstr ""
"Awal n unadi igber iberdiyen n ufraz n ubrid.\n"
"<b>Nadi deg ubrid</b> irmed i kra n wakud i wawal-a."

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:651
msgid "REGEX"
msgstr "TANFALIT TALUGANT"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:726
msgid ""
"The search was cancelled before it finished.\n"
"<b>These results are incomplete.</b>"
msgstr ""
"Anadi yettwasefsex send ad yemmed.\n"
"<b>Igmaḍ-a ur mmiden ara.</b>"

#: src/fsearch_statusbar.ui:756
msgid "PARTIAL"
msgstr "ARUMMID"

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:26
msgid "What's New in FSearch"
msgstr "Acu i d-amaynut deg FSearch"

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:79
msgid ""
"<span size=\"xx-large\" weight=\"bold\">What's New in FSearch 0.3</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span size=\"xx-large\" weight=\"bold\">Acu i d-amaynut deg FSearch 0.3</"
"span>"

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:149
msgid "<big><b>File System Monitoring</b></big>"
msgstr "<big><b>Aḍfar n unagraw n yifuyla</b></big>"

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:163
msgid ""
"You can now actively watch individual folders to eliminate frequent rescans. "
"File changes then appear in your search results immediately.\n"
"\n"
"To enable this feature go to the Database section of the Preferences "
"dialog.\n"
"\n"
"See the online documentation for more information:\n"
"<a href=\"URL\">https://github.com/cboxdoerfer/fsearch/wiki/Database-update</"
"a>"
msgstr ""
"Tzemreḍ tura ad tḍefreḍ ikaramen imaẓlayen akken ad tekkseḍ allus n unadi "
"yezgan. Imbeddlen n yifuyla ad d-banent din din deg yigmaḍ n unadi.\n"
"\n"
"I urmad n tmahilta-a, ddu ɣer tgezmi n taffa n yisefka deg usfaylu n "
"Yismenyifen.\n"
"\n"
"Wali tasemlit ɣef uẓeṭṭa i wugar n yisalan:\n"
"<a href=\"URL\">https://github.com/cboxdoerfer/fsearch/wiki/Database-update</"
"a>"

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:232
msgid "<big><b>Folder-Specific Rescan Schedules</b></big>"
msgstr "<big><b>Isuddisen n wallus n usiggez i yal akaram</b></big>"

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:246
msgid ""
"You can now configure automatic update intervals for individual folders "
"independently and tailored to each distinct location."
msgstr ""
"Tzemreḍ ad teswelḍ tura tallunin n uleqqem awurman i yal akaram s tlelli, s "
"usgadi i yal adig yemgaraden."

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:309
msgid "<big><b>Improved Exclude Rules</b></big>"
msgstr "<big><b>Ilugan n ustixxer yettwaseǧhden</b></big>"

#: src/fsearch_welcome_dialog.ui:323
msgid ""
"You can now use wildcards and regular expressions to define more powerful "
"exclude rules. \n"
"Rules can be targeted specifically at files, folders, or both, and can be "
"configured to match against either the basename or the full absolute path."
msgstr ""
"Tzemreḍ tura ad tesqedceḍ izamulen ilelliyen d tenfaliyin tiluganin i usbadu "
"n yilugan n ustixxer iǧehden ugar. \n"
"Ilugan zemren ad ttunefken s wudem usdid i yifuyla, i yikaramen, neɣ i sin, "
"yerna zemren ad ttuswelken akken ad mṣadan ama d yisem azadur ama d abrid "
"amagdez ummid."

#: src/fsearch_window.c:763 src/menus.ui:271
msgid "Extension"
msgstr "Asiɣzef"

